# Database Rules

- Prefer PostgreSQL-native features when useful.
- Use UUIDs for public entities.
- Use foreign keys internally.
- Use indexes intentionally.
- Avoid nullable fields when unnecessary.
- Use timestamps consistently.
- Keep migrations reversible.
- Bid history must remain immutable (no UPDATE/soft delete on `bids`).
- Auctions may soft-delete only when no active bids; see ADR-001.
- Use transactions for all bidding operations.
- `auctions.revision` integer for optimistic ordering (ADR-003).
